<question-stem>
<para> Why does the professor suggest that moveable type printing took a long
time to become common?<mediaExhibit frameType="mp3" mediaRef="toeflPrac10212.mp3"/></para>
</question-stem>
<answer-choice-set>
<answer-choice> Very few people understood how the printing presses worked.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> Scribes united to protect their manuscript copying business.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice correct="yes"> Early printers had a limited production capacity.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> People preferred handwritten books with colored illustrations.</answer-choice>
</answer-choice-set>
<explanation interaction="true">
<para> The professor states that the early printing presses had a hard time
keeping up with the demands, which indicates that the production capacity
was limiting their requests. The professor said that there weren't enough
people to copy books, not print them (A), and there is no mention of the scribes'
uniting to protect the copying business (B). The fact that some people prefer
handwritten books is not relevant (D).</para>
</explanation>
